    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-09T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-09T08:00:00-05:00" n="183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/10–951: Telegram</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 183</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName corresp="#p_BDKE1"
                            type="from">Bruce</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d183fn1">Repeated to <gloss target="#t_OSR1"
                        >OSR</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-09T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 9, 1951—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2082. In conversation with <persName corresp="#p_MR1">Rene Mayer</persName> over
                    week end he expressed same optimistic view of ratification of <persName
                        corresp="#p_SR1">Schuman</persName> Plan and European Army as that reported
                    by <persName corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BG1"
                        >Bidault</persName> in <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 2043, Oct
                        6.<note n="2" xml:id="d183fn2">Not printed.</note> He was preoccupied even
                    more than <persName corresp="#p_PR2">Pleven</persName> with polit consequences
                    that might follow from presentation to Parliament of 52 budget and balance of
                    payments prospects. Levels of govt expenditures, of possible tax revenues, of
                    econ activity and of <pb facs="0471" n="429" xml:id="pg_429"/> imports were all
                    interrelated and full picture of present situation wld have to be disclosed.
                        <persName corresp="#p_MR1">Mayer</persName> stated that he was still engaged
                    with <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> in drawing up an interim
                    military budget which wld be based on a minimum level of expenditures consistent
                    with present engagements of France in connection with European def. He
                    considered it unwise to attempt to do more until the Wisemen<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d183fn3">For documentation on the organization and activities of the
                            <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NATO</gloss> Temporary Council Committee (<gloss
                            target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss>), see <ref target="frus1951v03p1#pg_1">vol.
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, Part 1, pp. 1</ref> ff.</note> had
                    completed their report and at least initial action on report had been taken in
                    Rome or at a later <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NATO</gloss> conf. He said that, of
                    course, his decisions on import program at least for immediate period cld not
                    await completion of this exercise and he was anxious to have a statement of our
                    views on exact timing of US/French bilateral talks proposed for end of Oct. I
                    replied that we had no definite <gloss target="#t_instr1">instr</gloss>s from
                    Wash on timing of talks and suggested that French officials and <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>–<gloss
                        target="#t_MAAG1">MAAG</gloss> team prepare background balance of payments
                    and other info that wld be necessary when talks were undertaken.</p>
                <p>Mayer said he wld also like to proceed urgently with talks on financial
                    assistance to Indochina in order to complete aspects of Indochinese problem
                    raised by General <persName corresp="#p_DLDT1">de Lattre</persName> in
                        Wash.<note n="4" xml:id="d183fn4">See footnote 4, Document 179.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MR1">Mayer</persName> stated that it wld not be possible
                    to submit even an interim budget consistent with French engagements in Eur if
                    Indochinese expenditures borne by French Govt cld not be reduced to around 200
                    billion francs in 52.</p>
                <p>Mayer also mentioned that his many econ and financial difficulties were
                    complicated now by a tightening treasury position. He attributed this in part to
                    recent increase in wages or civil servants necessity for various deficiency
                    appropriations, subsidy for imported coal and an overoptimism with ref to tax
                    receipts from corporations. He assumed <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> bill
                    wld be signed in time for <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> mission to resume
                    release of counterpart for end of Oct.</p>
                <p>Mayer asked that US make an early regularization of its obligations under
                    agreement reached in Ottawa on infrastructure, and touched upon his recent
                    promise to Gen <persName corresp="#p_EGDD1">Eisenhower</persName> to use <gloss
                        target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> counterpart for <gloss target="#t_SHAPE1"
                        >SHAPE</gloss> housing. He is still hoping that he can obtain an early
                    priority in shipping to permit delivery of additional coal French intend to
                    purchase in US.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> mission and <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss> are reporting more fully on status of each of above
                    questions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
